ing the driver layer can still resolve without the fake module since the system loadClass might find a previous definition. To simplify things, I think I should check if systemClassLoader.loadClass(INSTALLER_TYPE) succeeds before adding the fake module. If it does, I can use the finder without the installer, just the driver roots. If it fails, I should create the fake module. If the initial definition uses the platform, subsequent loadClass checks will succeed. I also need to consider adding an optional check to ClassFileLocator to improve functionality.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_uVok2ZF6yrRStmlUVboquEX5|fc_001323b9b457a5c10169fc269285348191b442200555821dc7", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/ClassFileLocatorInnerForInstrumentationTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    private static final String INSTALLER_MODULE =\n            \"org.modelmapper.fakeagent\";", "newText": "    private static final String INSTALLER_MODULE =\n            \"org.modelmapper.fakeagent\";\n    private static final String INSTALLER_TYPE =\n            \"org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.agent.Installer\";"}, {"oldText": "                Path driverModule = driverModulePath(temporaryDirectory);\n                Path installerModule = installerModulePath(temporaryDirectory);\n                ModuleFinder finder = ModuleFinder.of(\n                        modelMapperModule,\n                        driverModule,\n                        installerModule);\n                Configuration configuration = ModuleLayer.boot()\n                        .configuration()\n                        .resolve(\n                                finder,\n                                ModuleFinder.of(),\n                                Set.of(DRIVER_MODULE, INSTALLER_MODULE));", "newText": "                Path driverModule = driverModulePath(temporaryDirectory);\n                Optional<Path> installerModule = installerModulePathIfNeeded(\n                        temporaryDirectory);\n                ModuleFinder finder = installerModule\n                        .map(path -> ModuleFinder.of(\n                                modelMapperModule,\n                                driverModule,\n                                path))\n                        .orElseGet(() -> ModuleFinder.of(\n                                modelMapperModule,\n                                driverModule));\n                Set<String> roots = installerModule.isPresent()\n                        ? Set.of(DRIVER_MODULE, INSTALLER_MODULE)\n                        : Set.of(DRIVER_MODULE);\n                Configuration configuration = ModuleLayer.boot()\n                        .configuration()\n                        .resolve(finder, ModuleFinder.of(), roots);"}, {"oldText": "    private static Path installerModulePath(Path temporaryDirectory) throws IOException {\n        Path installerJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"fakeagent.jar\");", "newText": "    private static Optional<Path> installerModulePathIfNeeded(\n            Path temporaryDirectory) throws IOException {\n        try {\n            ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader().loadClass(INSTALLER_TYPE);\n            return Optional.empty();\n        } catch (ClassNotFoundException missingInstaller) {\n            return Optional.of(installerModulePath(temporaryDirectory));\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Path installerModulePath(Path temporaryDirectory) throws IOException {\n        Path installerJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"fakeagent.jar\");"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 340, "output": 1329, "cacheRead": 55296, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 56965, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778132613301, "responseId": "resp_001323b9b457a5c10169fc26867418819183deba98ecff3f0f"}}
