[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Addressing code issues**\n\nI’m identifying a potential issue with UncheckedIOException in the copyJarEntries function, as it’s not converting to IOException. I need to import File, Arrays, and Optional. Also, I should update the AgentBuilder test to avoid using unnamed Installer, especially if the workflow reruns cleanly with the JVM. I think I’ll need to define a fake module within the layer, removing unnecessary ensures and making some tweaks. I’m pondering whether two modules with the same name and loader platform are allowed; that might be an important consideration.\n\n**Examining module loading**\n\nI’m considering if the first ClassFileLocator can define a fake agent for the platform loader while later attempts define the same module name in another layer. Can a single class loader actually load the same module name in multiple layers? It seems modules can repeat in different layers, but not if they're the same class loader due to package mapping issues. I think I need unique module names to avoid conflicts, especially if both tests define a fake installer. Maybe one can detect the already loaded module and skip adding it again.\n\n**Refining module resolution**\n\nI’m realizing the driver layer can still resolve without the fake module since the system loadClass might find a previous definition. To simplify things, I think I should check if systemClassLoader.loadClass(INSTALLER_TYPE) succeeds before adding the fake module. If it does, I can use the finder without the installer, just the driver roots. If it fails, I should create the fake module. If the initial definition uses the platform, subsequent loadClass checks will succeed. I also need to consider adding an optional check to ClassFileLocator to improve functionality.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_001323b9b457a5c10169fc268751fc81919b6a239823d5a32c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_con