[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Identifying class loading issues**\n\nI’m realizing that the system's loadClass method won’t find the class because it doesn’t delegate to the child. It seems that there was previous success because the fake installer was in the system classpath. In my modified code, the fake installer module is on the same layer as the loader's parent platform but not in the system. This is definitely a big issue that needs addressing!\n\n**Evaluating module system implementation**\n\nI'm considering the module system class loader lookup. It seems I should handle this appropriately. I might need to implement it for both tests. Alternatively, there's a simpler option: keeping the previous `ensureFakeInstallerOnSystemClassLoader` method, but renaming it could streamline things. I'm trying to balance simplicity with effectiveness here, and I want to ensure I'm not overcomplicating the process. It’s important to find the best solution!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_001323b9b457a5c10169fc26c45d648191b5ac0e769cf1db75\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_Cbko0RXw-eD_nNpQtzxHEtdveJN8eOciGNFE8-Ud6PGejevfZWpbvhuUHi8vN7t0GOgEHtF8qsheeSCppHkNAMuW3c10s9O2wBVxjK3nQbst0oS7d7gzirQ1o0b5Z0cVN7dNxAAKQUkgEjZUqCTHGASM4BmlDEctXSr2N6kdqiuQMraHRl_BbuYLlry5ZgMnRT-0ynNWsso4miZJEm0wMWhnDYYQj5GEYiNgwR1CkcRn6FnFTPiH3h68Ck-240-_uqVmOddmvT7Sy8WgmNr1PMzjBX9pW7xt5I8dyyxTmB3XI-91jwQxN80YKOadsb5g2Y_7fHCe3RiXA4mLNVoGoB9c76CQpsntFafiiOHtU-Hq_efqPQuWmCIRSeHy8criEgKHgr_1VB0ypOn_NF10ofIDWN5k8YIEBXVnSj7VDINQQ4n4cglaN78kUvzA0z1Xp1JgFU2sflZko7YIWuMnZylYpt7QyteLqmnhzZ86jmXhtYjkbRiqqG_2HwtTOMcrlNIQqaV1dY12cVGohLs_ZmcilQh49ns5wl-64GJe2yS-cGQvbX9jRzjBavkJk5TW-9W9veeXN78T1uKjdrNsGm04V_BpsKarhhpSrtosTU-cKvxe9fro5d1axpmM90_DRaY8PSO-YyfH6Bn2jz7BC8cp9tlylmBXI313UC_GQq-zFgm5FEUoC7AKct_KxIGf8MZQsdBM-yIr3dBhPhodJcOXYewPJiZjgjp9X8_gGjMeCv2h9tElW6rsMb1A0t_h3vOphECR3gPK28jxpVjUdHWLrGN9_YokeG1_nbCHdN69